<subSubSection id="C354650EA935FFAC0AEE14F9C966B4AD" pageId="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF13685A935FFAC0AEE14F9C966B4AD" blockId="2.[151,1436,389,846]" pageId="2">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0AEE14F9CC47B4D5" bold="true" box="[151,273,389,414]" pageId="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0B6314F9CCD7B4D6" box="[282,385,389,413]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Pediacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0B6314F9CCD7B4D6" box="[282,385,389,413]" italics="true" pageId="2">Pediacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species may be distinguished from the other two genera known from Asia and Australasia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0AEE14D5CDA5B48B" box="[151,243,425,448]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Cucujus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0AEE14D5CDA5B48B" box="[151,243,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="2">Cucujus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0B5314D5CCD2B48A" box="[298,388,425,449]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Platisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0B5314D5CCD2B48A" box="[298,388,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="2">Platisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the following characters: size small (length 
<quantity id="4CB69B60A935FFAC09D814D5C962B48A" box="[929,1076,425,450]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="2.6">2.6 –4.7 mm</quantity>
), temples absent or reduced to a small tooth-like projection, antennae with a well-developed three-segmented club.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354650EA935FFAC0ABE148DCEB2B765" pageId="2" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF13685A935FFAC0ABE148DCEB2B765" blockId="2.[151,1436,389,846]" pageId="2">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0ABE148DCC0FB741" bold="true" box="[199,345,497,522]" pageId="2">Description.</emphasis>
As for 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B74A935FFAC0BCA148DCF37B742" author="Thomas" box="[435,609,497,522]" pageId="2" refString="Thomas, M. C. (2004 [&quot; 2003 &quot;]) A revision of Pediacus Shuckard (Coleoptera: Cucujidae) for America north of Mexico, with notes on other species. Insecta Mundi, 17 (3 - 4), 157 - 177." type="journal article" year="2004">
Thomas (
<number id="3D8624A2A935FFAC0867148DCF0FB742" box="[542,601,497,521]" pageId="2" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but with the following changes: pronotum with anterior angle obtuse to acute; elytra broadly rounded to moderately costate or carinate sublaterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354650EA935FFAC0ABE1745C9A1B605" pageId="2" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BF13685A935FFAC0ABE1745C927B64E" blockId="2.[151,1436,389,846]" pageId="2">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0ABE1745CC71B719" bold="true" box="[199,295,569,594]" pageId="2">Biology.</emphasis>
There is little information available about the biology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC09C41745C972B71A" box="[957,1060,569,593]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Pediacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC09C41745C972B71A" box="[957,1060,569,593]" italics="true" pageId="2">Pediacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As for other cucujids, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0F4C1745C8CDB71A" box="[1333,1435,569,593]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Pediacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0F4C1745C8CDB71A" box="[1333,1435,569,593]" italics="true" pageId="2">Pediacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are apparently found under bark. In his revision of the North American fauna, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B74A935FFAC0E6A1721C997B73D" author="Thomas" box="[1043,1217,605,630]" pageId="2" refString="Thomas, M. C. (2004 [&quot; 2003 &quot;]) A revision of Pediacus Shuckard (Coleoptera: Cucujidae) for America north of Mexico, with notes on other species. Insecta Mundi, 17 (3 - 4), 157 - 177." type="journal article" year="2004">
Thomas (
<number id="3D8624A2A935FFAC0E071722C9EFB73D" box="[1150,1209,606,630]" pageId="2" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that they are predominantly found under bark of dead conifers. There is minimal collection data available among the specimens examined in this revision. This includes: ‘dead oak bark’; ‘large cut tree- 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC098917DAC918B7F6" box="[1008,1102,678,701]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC098917DAC918B7F6" box="[1008,1102,678,701]" italics="true" pageId="2">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.’; ‘on spruce’; ‘small cut sapling’; ‘light trap’; ‘insect flight trap’ and ‘sifted moss and bark’. Several specimens were collected from high altitudes, ranging up to 
<quantity id="4CB69B60A935FFAC0BD91792CCA1B64E" box="[416,503,750,774]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
, and for one species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC08911792CED3B64E" box="[744,901,750,773]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Pediacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivagus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC08911792CED3B64E" box="[744,901,750,773]" italics="true" pageId="2">P. montivagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ca. 
<quantity id="4CB69B60A935FFAC09C01791C93BB64E" box="[953,1133,749,774]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="2" unit="m" value="3050.0" valueMax="3600.0" valueMin="2500.0">2500 to 3600 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF13685A935FFAC0ABE166DC9A1B605" blockId="2.[151,1436,389,846]" pageId="2">
Little is known about 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0BC5166DCF75B662" box="[444,547,785,809]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Pediacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0BC5166DCF75B662" box="[444,547,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="2">Pediacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae. They are likely to be predacious, as is apparently the case for the larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0ACC164ACC47B606" box="[181,273,822,845]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Cucujus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0ACC164ACC47B606" box="[181,273,822,845]" italics="true" pageId="2">Cucujus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D06A935FFAC0B3E1649CE65B605" authority="Marris &amp; Klimaszewski" authorityName="Marris &amp; Klimaszewski" box="[327,819,821,846]" class="Insecta" family="Cucujidae" genus="Platisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zelandicus">
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0B3E1649CF49B606" box="[327,543,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="2">Platisus zelandicus</emphasis>
Marris &amp; Klimaszewski
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B74A935FFAC09381649C97EB605" author="Smith" box="[833,1064,821,846]" pageId="2" refString="Smith, D. B. &amp; Sears, M. K. (1982) Mandibular structure and feeding habits of three morphologically similar coleopterous larvae: Cucujus clavipes (Cucujidae), Dendroides canadensis (Pyrochroidae), and Pytho depressus (Salpingidae). Canadian Entomologist, 114, 173 - 175. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4039 / ent 114173 - 2" type="journal article" year="1982">
Smith &amp; Sears 
<number id="3D8624A2A935FFAC0994164AC97EB605" box="[1005,1064,822,846]" pageId="2" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B74A935FFAC0E4D164AC9BCB605" author="Watt" box="[1076,1258,821,846]" pageId="2" refString="Watt, J. C., Marris, J. W. M. &amp; Klimaszewski, J. (2001) A new species of Platisus (Coleoptera: Cucujidae) from New Zealand, described from the adult and larva. Journal of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 31, 327 - 339. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.2001.9517657" type="journal article" year="2001">
Watt 
<emphasis id="B93AEA97A935FFAC0E16164AC9FEB606" box="[1135,1192,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3D8624A2A935FFAC0ED7164AC9BCB605" box="[1198,1258,822,846]" pageId="2" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
